This paper discusses the integration of Software-Defined Networking (SDN) and Information-Centric Networking (ICN), which are both relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the protocol and mechanisms required for this integration, which could fall under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The scalability and dynamic management of the network topology could also be relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The integration of ICN and SDN could also involve system-level design and control, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and validation of a proof-of-concept prototype, which could be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
